# Healthcare Analytics Dashboard (Excel)

## Overview
- Built an interactive Excel dashboard to analyze simulated healthcare patient data.
- The dashboard enables dynamic exploration of patient visits, malaria positivity rates, anemia prevalence, and hemoglobin distribution using slicers and pivot charts.

## Dataset
- Simulated clinical dataset containing 300 patient records.
- Variables include patient demographics, visit dates, ward admissions, malaria test results, and hemoglobin levels.

## Tools Used
- Microsoft Excel
- Pivot Tables
- Pivot Charts
- Slicers
- Data visualization

## Key Metrics
- Total patient visits
- Malaria positivity rate
- Anemia prevalence
- Average hemoglobin level

## Visualizations
- Visits by ward (column chart)
- Malaria positivity by age group (stacked column chart)
- Monthly patient visit trends (line chart)
- Hemoglobin distribution (histogram)

## Dashboard Preview
- Interactive dashboard with slicers for filtering by sex, ward, and malaria status.

## Insights
- Malaria positivity appeared higher among younger patients in the dataset.
- Some wards recorded higher patient visit volumes than others.
- Hemoglobin distribution suggests a moderate prevalence of anemia.

## Future Improvements
- Rebuild the dashboard using Power BI for more advanced interactivity.
- Automate data cleaning using Python or Power Query.
- Integrate SQL-based data sources for scalable healthcare analytics.
